00:28:26,586 --> 00:28:29,068
be put on top of
an exploding rocket

365
00:28:29,103 --> 00:28:31,103
that is going to
hurtle it into space.

366
00:28:40,241 --> 00:28:43,344
Lift-off for
the Delta II rocket
with Kepler,

367
00:28:43,379 --> 00:28:46,655
on a search for planets
in some way like our own.

368
00:28:47,896 --> 00:28:50,793
The launch
of the Kepler space telescope

369
00:28:50,827 --> 00:28:55,275
might just be remembered
as the beginning
of the biggest discovery

370
00:28:55,310 --> 00:28:58,896
in astronomy in our lifetime,

371
00:28:58,931 --> 00:29:04,931
peering further into space
than any optical telescope
on Earth.

372
00:29:04,965 --> 00:29:08,206
Kepler began its search
for faraway worlds.

373
00:29:12,586 --> 00:29:16,206
And it was really Kepler
that opened its eye,

374
00:29:16,241 --> 00:29:18,827
and then suddenly
started to find

375
00:29:18,862 --> 00:29:23,413
world after world,
these thousands of planets
that we never knew existed,

376
00:29:23,448 --> 00:29:27,448
and that imply the existence
of billions of planets more.

377
00:29:27,482 --> 00:29:29,655
So it really,
really changed
the game

378
00:29:29,689 --> 00:29:32,275
and really opened up
the universe to us.

379
00:29:42,310 --> 00:29:46,206
Kepler discovered
